## Control Flow

Control flow determines the order in which code executes. Swift provides several ways to control execution.

### If Statements

```swift
let temperature = 25
if temperature > 30 {
    print("Hot day!")
} else if temperature > 20 {
    print("Nice weather")
} else {
    print("Cold day")
}
```

### Switch Statements

Switch is powerful for matching multiple conditions:

```swift
let grade = "A"
switch grade {
case "A": print("Excellent!")
case "B": print("Good job")
case "C": print("Passed")
default: print("Keep trying")
}
```

### Pattern Matching

```swift
let point = (2, 3)
switch point {
case (0, 0): print("Origin")
case (_, 0): print("On X-axis")
case (0, _): print("On Y-axis")
default: print("Somewhere else")
}
```

